<TITLE> Lightning kills four people in Mymensingh </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Mymensingh, June 3 (bdnews24.com)  Lightning tore through three villages in Mymensingh Sadar upazila Sunday, leaving four young boys dead and five people injured, a police official said. Rafique, 16, Manir, 13, Rabbi, 14, and Rafique, 15, died instantly after the lightning hit Charjel Khana village, the district's police chief Rafiqul Islam said. All of them were working in a field when it hit the village. Nargis, 25, Roksana, 15, and Mahmuda, 13, of Dapunia village and Halima Khatun, 40 and Rabia Khatun, 45, of Shombhuganj village were seriously injured in separate thunderbolts. bdnews2
